[? if nfvp_formed and dvp_leader = "Raumer": <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**NFVP**</span> - <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);"><i>Nationalfortschrittliche Volkspartei</i></span> (National Progressive People's Party) - This is us. Formed with members of the <span style="color: #DCCA4A;">**German Democrats**</span> and Front 1929 with the assistance the <span style="color: #D3D3A9;">**Young German Order**</span>, [? if peoples_conservatives_dvp: and the moderate splinters of the <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>, ?] we are the representatives of the German middle class and the party of the parliamentarian right. With the shock election of Von Raumer as party leader, the <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**NFVP**</span> has jolted to the right, with heavy industry flooding into the party. The [? if kvp_formed: <span style="color: #455B95;">**KVP**</span>?][? if not kvp_formed: <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>?] and national opposition have voiced approval at this, as the party shifts further right than ever before, the left-wing of the party are in uproar with Lemmer and Thiel in particular being enraged at this development. It seems the deadlock that has plagued the german liberal movement is alive and well. ?]
[? if nfvp_formed and dvp_leader = "Treviranus": <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**NFVP**</span> - <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);"><i>Nationalfortschrittliche Volkspartei</i></span> (National Progressive People's Party) - This is us. Formed with members of the <span style="color: #DCCA4A;">**German Democrats**</span> and Front 1929 with the assistance the <span style="color: #D3D3A9;">**Young German Order**</span>, [? if peoples_conservatives_dvp: and the moderate splinters of the <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>, ?] we are the representatives of the German middle class and the party of the parliamentarian right. With Gottfried Trevarinus being elected to the leadership of the <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**NFVP**</span>, the party has shifted to the right; this has come as a shock to many of Germany’s political class, as they were often on the fringe of the various parties the movement is now spread across - but now, they seem to have found a political home in the <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**NFVP**</span>. Trevarinus will try to work with the Bürgerblock parties if possible - being an Anti-Marxist, he will try avoid co-operation with the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> if possible. This has caused some dissent amongst the Democrats and Progressives. However, he is a commited republican and this helps keep dissent low. ?]
[? if nfvp_formed and dvp_leader = "Luther": <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**NFVP**</span> - <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);"><i>Nationalfortschrittliche Volkspartei</i></span> (National Progressive People's Party) - This is us. Formed with members of the <span style="color: #DCCA4A;">**German Democrats**</span> and Front 1929 with the assistance the <span style="color: #D3D3A9;">**Young German Order**</span>, [? if peoples_conservatives_dvp: and the moderate splinters of the <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>, ?] we are the representatives of the German middle class and the party of the parliamentarian right. With former chancellor Hans Luther’s election as a compromise candidate, and his duties [? if not president="Luther":at the Reichsbank?][? if president="Luther": as President?], he is set to hold a hands-off approach to leadership, with representatives from all factions such as Dietrich and Curtius helping with day-to-day running. Luther is greatly respected by all factions, and this ensures he can command great respect. This, however, is not enough to prevent him being seen as a compromise candidate. ?]

<span style="color: #8B0000;">**KPD**</span> - <span style="color: #8B0000;">*Kommunistische Partei Deutschlands*</span> (German Communist Party) - a radical left-wing offshoot of the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> that emerged in the aftermath of the German Revolution of 1918, they follow the path of Moscow, opposing parliamentary democracy in favor of a Soviet-style revolution.

Current relations: [+ kpd_relation: relationships +]

<span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> - <span style="color: #E3000F;">*Sozialdemokratische Partei Deutschlands*</span> (Social Democratic Party of Germany) - a socialist and democratic party of the working class. They are the heirs of the legacy of Marx and Engels, Lassalle and Bebel. They are the foremost defenders of the Republic. The modern <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> was formed from a merger of the "Majority" <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>, which supported the Great War, and the "Independent" <span style="color: #C40000;">**SPD**</span> or <span style="color: #C40000;">**USPD**</span>, which opposed the war.

Current relations: [+ spd_relation : relationships +]

[? if aspd_exist: <span style="color: #FE9E00;">**ASPD**</span> - <span style="color: #FE9E00;"><i>Alte Sozialdemokratische Partei Deutschlands</i></span> (Old Social Democratic Party of Germany) - a labour-nationalist Saxony-based party borne through disagreements with the local <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> branch. They are an oddity within the political sphere: combining proletarian appeals with Völkisch nationalism and a renunciation of Marxism. [? if aspd_ideology = "Moderate": Recently, the <span style="color: #FE9E00;">**ASPD**</span> has resurfaced under Max Heldt, departing from its national-revolutionary or social fascist positions. They are drifting towards the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> in terms of ideological direction, participating in Saxony’s state elections as a more moderate alternative to the Saxon <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>. ?][? if aspd_ideology = "Radical": Recently, the <span style="color: #FE9E00;">**ASPD**</span> has resurfaced under Ernst Niekisch, retaining its national-revolutionary character under Niekisch’s guidance. Their reemergence will be brief, curious labour unions in Saxony have already left the <span style="color: #FE9E00;">**ASPD**</span> to rot. ?] ?]

[? if aspd_exist: Current relations: [+ aspd_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if ddp_exist: <span style="color: #DCCA4A;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span> - <span style="color: #DCCA4A;"><i>Deutsche Demokratische Partei</i></span> (German Democratic Party) - a center-left liberal party, popular among the intelligensia and educated middle class. They have often been in coalitions with us. [? if dstp_formed : They have recently reformed themselves as the German State Party (DStP). ?] ?]

[? if ddp_exist: Current relations: [+ ddp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if dbp_exist: <span style="color: #38C538;">**DBP**</span> - <span style="color: #38C538;"><i>Deutsche Bauernpartei</i></span> (German Farmers' Party) - a liberal and strongly non-clerical agrarian party founded by the representatives of <span style="color: #38C538;">**BB**</span> (Bavarian Peasants' League) to expand its electoral base. The party supports the republic. ?]

[? if dbp_exist: Current relations: [+ dbp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if csrp_exist: <span style="color: #FF6B21;">**CSRP**</span> - <span style="color: #FF6B21;"><i>Christlich-Soziale Reichspartei</i></span> (Christian Social Reich Party) - a center-left party splintering from <span style="color: #000000;">**Z**</span> due to alienation from the clerical and interconfessional labour wings. They promote Catholic Social Doctrine, greater social security, and labour unions. Currently, they have united under Joseph Wirth, an infamous former Chancellor known for his temporary defection to the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>. ?]

[? if csrp_exist: Current relations: [+ csrp_relation : relationships +] ?]

<span style="color: #000000;">**Z**</span> - <span style="color: #000000;">*Zentrumspartei*</span> (Center Party) - a centrist to center-right Catholic party that supports the Republic. They have often been in coalitions with us. They are often associated with the <span style="color: #69A2BE;">**BVP**</span> (Bavarian People's Party), which represents Catholics in Bavaria.

Current relations: [+ z_relation : relationships +]

[? if csvd_exist: <span style="color: #8ED8E4;">**CSVD**</span> - <span style="color: #8ED8E4;"><i>Christlich-Sozialer Volksdienst</i></span> (Christian Social People's Service) - a centre-right party, formed by members of the Christian Social faction of <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>. The party supports state welfare, trade unions and workers participation in management. ?]

[? if csvd_exist: Current relations: [+ csvd_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if wp_exist: <span style="color: #B8996F;">**WP**</span> - <span style="color: #B8996F;"><i>Wirtschaftspartei</i></span> (Economic Party) - a small conservative party that emerged from small and medium-sized business interest groups that had achieved political success in the Berlin area since 1920. The <span style="color: #B8996F;">**WP**</span> limits itself to representing the interests of homeowners, landowners, craftsmen, and small business owners and is located in the bourgeois-right spectrum. [? if wp_ideology = "Radical": Recently, the party has made a turn to the right. ?] ?]

[? if wp_exist: Current relations: [+ wp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if cnblp_exist: <span style="color: #7FCEB1;">**CNBLP**</span> - <span style="color: #7FCEB1;"><i>Christlich-Nationale Bauern- und Landvolkpartei</i></span> (Christian-National Peasants' and Farmers' Party) - an agrarian conservative party representing interests of the Protestant rural population, mostly the small and medium farmers. ?]

[? if cnblp_exist: Current relations: [+ cnblp_relation : relationships +] ?]

[? if kvp_formed: <span style="color: #455B95;">**KVP**</span> - <span style="color: #455B95;"><i>Konservative Volkspartei</i></span> (Conservative People's Party) - a party recently formed in a split from the <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>, the <span style="color: #455B95;">**KVP**</span> is essentially an agglomeration of moderate conservative groups. ?]

[? if kvp_formed: Current relations: [+ kvp_relation : relationships +] ?]

<span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span> - <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">*Deutschnationale Volkspartei*</span> (German National People's Party) - a right-wing nationalist-conservative party, with authoritarian, monarchist, and racist elements. It is supported by the former aristocracy, rural landowners, and conservative Lutherans. We have occasionally been in coalitions.

Current relations: [+ dnvp_relation : relationships +]

[? if dnf_formed: <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span> - <span style="color: #003755;"><i>Deutschnationale Front</i></span> (German National Front) - a far-right nationalist-conservative party, led by Alfred Hugenberg, originally split from the <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>. It is supported by a small but loyal base of Hugenberg supporters, consisting of former aristocrats, racists and nationalists. ?]

[? if dnf_formed: Current relations: [+ dnf_relation : relationships +] ?]

<span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span> - <span style="color: #954B00;">*Nationalsozialistische Deutsche Arbeiterpartei*</span> (National Socialist German Worker's Party, or Nazis) - a far-right nationalist and antisemitic party. Led by Adolf Hitler, they attempted a coup in 1923, and were banned for it, but have since been legalized.

Current relations: [+ nsdap_relation : relationships +]

<span style="color: #909090;">**Other parties**</span> - there is a multitude of other small parties.

