Overall dissent: [+ dissent_percent : dissent +]

[? if nationalists_dvp: **Nationalists** ?]

[? if nationalists_dvp: Nationalists are on the extreme right of our party. Many support closer ties with the national opposition, and severing all ties with the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span> and even the <span style="color: #000000;">**Z**</span> and <span style="color: #DCCA4A;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>. They often oppose bourgoise and liberal unity. Recently, they have aligned themselves with the industrialists in our party, to try and weaken the Stresemanite wings of our party. Stresemann’s focus on foreign policy has caused their influence to grow in recent years. ?]

[? if nationalists_dvp: Strength: [+ nationalist_strength : strength +] ?]

[? if nationalists_dvp: Dissent: [+ nationalist_dissent : dissent +] ?]

[? if industrialists_dvp: **Industrialists** ?]

[? if industrialists_dvp: Industrialists are positioned on the centre-right of our party. The industrialists themselves are not involved too much in party politics, preferring to fund the party and subtly try to influence our direction. They support low taxes on the rich, and often no welfare state; for this, the weimar coalition parties have grown distrustful of us, with their influence growing recently. They often oppose bourgoise unity, but if the liberal movement was to undergo a decline, they may end up supporting it. ?]

[? if industrialists_dvp: Strength: [+ industrialist_strength : strength +] ?]

[? if industrialists_dvp: Dissent: [+ industrialist_dissent : dissent +] ?]

[? if labor_dvp: **Labor** ?]

[? if labor_dvp: The <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**[+ dvp_name +]**</span> has several affiliated trade unions; the largest of which is the DHV. They are often the antithesis of the industrialists, and sometimes favour more progressive taxation with a healthy welfare state. They are often supportive of cooperation with the weimar coalition parties, and liberal or bourgeois unity. Many labour members are also close allies of the Liberals, helping to fend off the industrialists from completely taking over the party for now. ?]

[? if labor_dvp: Strength: [+ labor_strength : strength +] ?]

[? if labor_dvp: Dissent: [+ labor_dissent : dissent +] ?]

[? if liberals_dvp: **Liberals** ?]

[? if liberals_dvp: The centre of our party, the liberals are believers in the Stresemannite message; a party of reason and republicanism. They are some of the foremost supporters of the republic within the <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**[+ dvp_name +]**</span>, and often passionately support liberal and bourgeois unity. They also support cooperation with the <span style="color: #E3000F;">**SPD**</span>, even if it is reluctantly. Most of our party is comprised of Liberals. They are descended from the pre-war <span style="color: #98C22C;">**NLP**</span>, with some - such as Stresemann - holding monarchist ideals. ?]

[? if liberals_dvp: Strength: [+ liberal_strength : strength +] ?]

